English Teacher - Part time ( Freelance)
- ,
Date Posted: 2014/04/30 06:28:57
Ref. JB3045708
Job Description
Abu Dhabi University Knowledge Group in the United Arab Emirates (UAE) is looking for part-time English language teachers, available between 29th of June and 17th of July.
ADUKG is involved in work with the wider community and university students. Experience with learners in the adult education sector is an important criteria for applicants.
We are looking for an individual with the right combination of skills and qualifications. Please do not send resumes if you cannot meet these criteria since we will be unable to respond.
Skills
Skills and Compensation
• CELTA certification, the UCLES DELTA certificate OR an attested Masters level qualification in Applied Linguistics. Please note that for those holding certifcate level qualifications, the UCLES CELTA certificate is the only certificate we recognise.
• Native speakers
• A COMPLETED Bachelors degree (not necessarily in English).
• Able to tolerate a high degree of ambiguity
• The ability to make very dry teaching materials come alive.
• Tolerant and easygoing - strong intercultural communication skills and ability to adapt.
Compensation:
For International Candidates : Package USD$2000 plus round ticket and hotel accommodation.
For Local Candidates : an hourly rate of 180 AED , 6 hours a day.
